overview: The user wanted to enhance their Sleep Questionnaire Application by
  adding a database to store responses, an admin dashboard for data access, and
  an authentication system. The assistant evaluated the existing codebase,
  identified missing components, and created a detailed plan. Key
  implementations included updating demographic data fields, creating a
   model in Prisma, developing API endpoints for saving,
  retrieving, and exporting responses as CSV, and building a simple admin login
  and dashboard UI. A significant pivot occurred in the authentication strategy,
  moving from a custom HMAC-signed session to a simpler Next.js middleware-based
  approach with a basic cookie, streamlining route protection. The assistant
  also guided the user through database setup with NeonDB and verified the
  connection, culminating in a successful browser-based test of questionnaire
  submission and admin dashboard functionality.
